-- Bank of Canada Buys C$475 Million of Securities for One Day
-- B y   C h r i s   F o u r n i e r
-- 2013-02-21T17:25:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-21/bank-of-canada-buys-c-475-million-of-securities-for-one-day.html
The Bank of  Canada  bought C$475
million ($466 million) of securities for one day.  The central bank announced the purchase, aimed to keep
overnight lending rates close to its current target of 1
percent, on its website today from Ottawa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Fournier in Ottawa at 
 cfournier3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
